h3. Summary

Confluence uses following format to express an anchor link in non-English(multi-byte) page title
{code:none}
pages/viewpage.action?pageId=<pageid>#id-<Page title>-<Anchored heading>{code}
while it's expressed as below when the title is all in English.
{code:none}
pages/viewpage.action?pageId=<pageid>#<Page title>-<Anchored heading>{code}
When you paste the former link then Confluence auto-convert the url wrongly and it doesn't navigate correctly to anchor.
{code:none}
pages/viewpage.action?pageId=<pageid>#id-<Page title>-<Page title>-<Anchored heading>{code}
h3. Steps to Reproduce
 # Create a page with page title "あ" and following contents.
{code:xml}
<p><ac:link ac:anchor="Heading1" /></p>
<h1>Heading1</h1>
{code}
 # Copy the URL from the page above. It will be like
{code:none}
http://<confluence-url>/pages/viewpage.action?pageId=<pageid>#id-あ-Heading1{code}
 # Create a new page and paste the above in it.

h3. Expected Results

The page in step 3 has a proper anchor link to "Heading1" and user can go to the page in step 1.
h3. Actual Results
It doesn't navigate to "Heading1". Just go to the page in step 1.
 This is because the link is wrong format as below.
{code:none}
http://<confluence-url>/pages/viewpage.action?pageId=<pageid>#id-あ-あ-Heading1{code}

h3. Note
Regular format link URL as below works fine. It work as expected result. 
{code:none}
pages/viewpage.action?pageId=<pageid>#<Page title>-<Anchored heading>
{code}
 
h3. Workaround
Use just English characters for page title.

h3. Summary
The Notifications/workbox icon is missing from fresh installs of Confluence 6.6.6

h3. Environment
* Confluence 6.6.6

h3. Steps to Reproduce
# Install Confluence 6.6

h3. Expected Results
The notification icon will be seen

h3. Actual Results
The notification icon is missing

!MissingIcon.png|thumbnail!

 h3.Workaround

 Add the following to the HEAD section in Custom HTML.

{code}
<script type="text/javascript">
    $(function(){
        $('#header .aui-iconfont-notification').addClass('aui-iconfont-workbox-empty');
    });
</script> 
{code}

When we change the color of the *Heading Text* in the color schemes section, *(Confluence_BaseURL)/admin/lookandfeel.action*, the color only applies to H1 to H4, and not for H5 and H6.

 !heading_color.png|thumbnail! 

*Workaround:*
Use inline CSS to set the color of Heading 5 and Heading 6 in the Global Stylesheet.
*(Confluence_BaseURL)/admin/viewstylesheet.action*.

{code:java}
h5 {
    color: red !important;
}

h6 {
    color: red !important;
}
{code}
